Title : North Dakota Library Association
Text : The '''North Dakota Library Association'''<ref name="ala">{{cite web|url=http://www.ala.org/groups/affiliates/chapters/state/stateregional|title=State and regional chapters &#124; Member Groups &amp; Communities|publisher=ala.org|accessdate=2014-10-31|date=2006-08-03}}</ref><ref>https://books.google.com/books?isbn=0838910580</ref><ref>https://books.google.com/books?isbn=0313097003</ref> (NDLA) is a professional association for librarians, library staff, and library supporters that represent school, public, academic, and special libraries located in [[North Dakota]], United States. "The purpose of this organization is to exercise professional leadership and to promote library services and librarianship."<ref name="ndla">{{cite web|url=http://ndla.info/constitution.php|title=NDLA Constitution|publisher=ndla.info|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref> The North Dakota Library Association was formed on January 18, 1906.<ref name="ndla2">{{cite web|url=http://ndla.info/good-stuff/gsaugust05.pdf|date=31 May 2005|title=The Good Stuff -August 2005|publisher=North Dakota Library Association|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref>  The association has humble beginnings – at the 1909 conference, there was only 18 members.<ref name="ndla3">{{cite web|url=http://ndla.info/good-stuff/gsdecember05.pdf|date=19 December 2005|title=THE OFFICIAL MAGAZINE OF THE NORTH DAKOTA LIBRARY ASSOCIATION|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref> There are currently over 300 NDLA members (including academic, health, public, and school libraries).<ref name="ndla.">{{cite web|url=http://ndla.info/good-stuff/gsdecember13.pdf|date=4 December 2013|volume=43|issue=4|title=THE OFFICIAL MAGAZINE OF THE NORTH DAKOTA LIBRARY|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref>

==Executive Board==

The NDLA Executive Board includes 27 members, including: President; President-Elect; Past President; Secretary; Treasurer; [[American Library Association]] Councilor; [[Mountain Plains Library Association]]<ref name="mpla">{{cite web|url=http://www.mpla.us/about/|title=MPLA: About the Association|publisher=mpla.us|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref> Representative; Academic & Special Libraries Section; Government Documents Roundtable; Health Science Information Section; New Members Roundtable; Public Library Section; School & Library Youth Service Section; Technical Services Roundtable; Constitution, Bylaws & Policies; Continuing Education; Finance; [[Intellectual Freedom]];<ref name="ala2">{{cite web|url=http://www.ala.org/offices/oif|title=Office for Intellectual Freedom &#124; Offices of the American Library Association|publisher=ala.org|accessdate=2014-10-31|date=2008-06-09}}</ref> Legislative; Nominations, Elections & Voting; Membership; Professional Development; Public Relations & 2014–26 Executive Secretary; The Good Stuff<ref name="tandfonline">{{cite journal|title=A Review of State and Regional Library Association Periodicals| doi=10.1080/00987913.1984.10763523|volume=10| issue=2|journal=Serials Review|pages=5–16|year = 1984|last1 = Ford|first1 = Karin E.}}</ref> Editorial; Archivist/Historian; State Librarian;<ref name="nd">{{cite web|url=http://library.nd.gov/statelibrarian.html|title=Meet the State Librarian - North Dakota State Library|publisher=library.nd.gov|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref> and Web Editor.<ref name="ndla4">{{cite web|url=http://ndla.info/ExecutiveH.pdf|date=17 September 2014|title=NDLA Executive Board|author=The Library|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref>
The Executive Board is responsible for the transactions of “all business of the North Dakota Library Association”, speaking “for the NDLA membership on national, state, and local library issues”, setting “goals and executes long-range plans for the NDLA”, taking “no position on social issues that do not directly impact libraries” and following “through on directives expressed by NDLA members at the Annual Conference and by section and roundtable decision.”  The Executive Board “meets at least three times a year” and “all meetings are open to the NDLA membership.”<ref name="ndla5">{{cite web|url=http://ndla.info/handbooks/ExBdpolicies.pdf|date=31 January 2013|title=POLICIES HANDBOOK: EXECUTIVE BOARD SCOPE OF RESPONSIBILITIES|author=Library of the Health Sciences|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref>

